cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with image generation and manipulation using generative models, specifically GANs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of style-generators, which are a recent development in GANs, and their potential as image priors. This suggests that the paper could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of linear identity-pose relations and animation of facial images, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
